This paper will describe how the Product Engineering Department of an Automotive Accessory Manufacturer, has utilized computer graphics to aid in the design and drafting of a variety of products. It will briefly describe the general justification for obtaining equipment, what equipment is being used, and the organization for using it, and typical applications in both design and drafting. Five problems related to using computer graphics will be discussed followed by a description of three techniques that have been used to improve system efficiency. In closing, it will look at some problems related with using computer graphics as well as its future, as seen from a authors view point.